SMURF is not so much a format for a single file but rather defines a hierarchy
of files that together provide information on different aspects of a robot. Thus a
SMURF robot definition consists of one main .smurf file containing general data
on the model and a list of files that should be included in the SMURF
representation of the robot. At a minimum, a .urdf file that defines the robots
kinematics is listed here. Normally, the list will also contain other files -
encoded in the YAML format - defining different parts of the robots such as
sensors, motors or additional data, e.g. simulation parameters

objects (not only robots) defined in the SMURF file.
